  "text": "The SpiderMonkey JavaScript engine compiles source text to bytecode through a well-defined pipeline in mozilla-firefox/firefox. The process begins with CompileGlobalScript() in js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:532, which orchestrates the entire compilation flow.\n\nThe compilation chain operates as follows:\n\n1. PARSER ENTRY POINT: CompileGlobalScript() at js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:532 calls CompileGlobalScriptImpl() which delegates to CompileGlobalScriptToStencilAndMaybeInstantiate() at line 303. This function creates a ScriptCompiler<Unit> instance (line 328) and invokes compiler.compile(maybeCx, &globalsc) at line 341.\n\n2. PARSING PHASE: ScriptCompiler<Unit>::compile() at js/src/frontend/BytecodeCompiler.cpp:955 manages the actual parsing. It calls parser->globalBody() (Parser.cpp:1867) for global scripts or parser->evalBody() (Parser.cpp:1776) for eval scripts. These methods use GeneralParser<ParseHandler, Unit>::parse() defined in Parser.h and implemented in Parser.cpp.\n\n3. AST NODES: The parser generates abstract syntax tree nodes of type ParseNode defined in js/src/frontend/ParseNode.h:712. ParseNode is the base class for all syntax tree node types. The ParseNodeKind enum at ParseNode.h:255 defines the various node type constants. Concrete node types include NumericLiteral, BinaryExpression, and others that represent the structure of the parsed JavaScript code.\n\n4. BYTECODE EMISSION: After parsing completes successfully, ScriptCompiler<Unit>::compile() creates a BytecodeEmitter instance at line 1004 via emplaceEmitter() and calls emitter->emitScript(pn) at line 1009. BytecodeEmitter is declared in js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.h:77-101 and implemented in js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.cpp. The emitScript() method at BytecodeEmitter.cpp:2354 traverses the ParseNode tree and generates bytecode sequences into the bytecode buffer.\n\n5. JSCRIPT OUTPUT: The final bytecode is encapsulated in a JSScript object defined in js/src/vm/JSScript.h:1787. JSScript inherits from BaseScript and contains the compiled bytecode accessible via code() at JSScript.h:1844. The bytecode is stored as jsbytecode* (unsigned char array) and the script maintains metadata about its code length via length() at line 1863. JSScript objects are instantiated via JSScript::Create() at line 1800 or JSScript::fromStencil() at line 1826, which consumes the compilation stencil to produce the final executable script object.\n\nThe entire chain is coordinated through the CompilationStencil intermediate representation, which collects parsed nodes, bytecode, and metadata during compilation. This stencil is then instantiated into actual JSScript and related runtime objects when used by the JavaScript runtime."
}

